New york city comprises 5 boroughs sitting where the Hudson River meets the Atlantic ocean. san Fransisco

San Francisco is a major city in the state of California, located on the west coast of the United States. It is the fourth-most populous city in California and the 16th-most populous city in the United States. San Francisco is known for its hilly terrain, iconic landmarks, diverse culture, and vibrant arts and music scene.

Chicago

Located on the shore of Lake Michigan, Chicago was incorporated as a city in 1837 near a portage between the Great Lakes and the Mississippi River watershed. It grew rapidly in the mid-19th century.In 1871, the Great Chicago Fire destroyed several square miles and left more than 100,000 homeless, but Chicago's population continued to grow.
